  "texts": [
    "Recently, Large Language Models (LLMs) have been applied to graphstructured data, either in hybrid approaches with GNNs (He et al. 2024; Yang et al.",
    "2024) or directly via textual graph encodings (Zhao et al. 2024; Fatemi et al.",
    "A growing focus is on graph reasoning, i.e., structural inference tasks such as shortest paths or subgraph counting.",
    "These both serve as representatives of complex reasoning with dependencies (Besta et al.",
    "2024; Sanford et al. 2024) and as tests of whether LLMs can capture structural patterns beyond the limits of GNNs."
  ],
